SKILL|vercel-deployment|Deploy Next.js apps to Vercel — build troubleshooting, serverless compatibility, dependency fixes, CI/GitHub integration, dashboard embedding patterns.
STEP|1|Next.js build passes locally but fails on Vercel
STEP|2|Deploying dashboards, metrics pages, or live-data panels into a Next.js app
STEP|3|GitHub Actions CI failures blocking deployment
STEP|4|Dependency problems (native modules, `file:` references) on serverless
STEP|5|Vercel auto-deploy stalls or shows stale statuses
STEP|6|Symptom:** Build errors referencing `better-sqlite3`, `bcrypt`, `sharp`, or any C++ addon.
STEP|7|Fix:** Remove the dependency or make it optional. Native modules that compile C++ cannot run on Vercel's serverless runtime.
STEP|8|Symptom:** `express`, `ws`, `socket.io` in a Next.js project.
STEP|9|Fix:** Next.js has its own API routes — you don't need Express. For real-time data, use REST polling (30s interval) instead of WebSocket. Vercel serverless functions don't maintain persistent connecti
STEP|10|Symptom:** `npm ci` fails on GitHub Actions with "Could not resolve `file:../some-package`".
STEP|11|Fix:** Use `github:org/repo#branch` for packages that aren't on npm yet:
STEP|12|Pattern:** Use REST polling, not WebSocket. Create a lightweight API route that returns stats.
STEP|13|Symptom:** Vercel deployment fails with cron-related errors.
STEP|14|Fix:** Check every cron path in `vercel.json` — each must have a corresponding `.ts` route handler:
STEP|15|Symptom:** GitHub shows "Vercel: failure" but the latest commit wasn't actually deployed.
STEP|16|Fix:** Go to the Vercel dashboard → project → Deployments → "Redeploy" on the latest commit. Or run `npx vercel --prod` from the CLI.
STEP|17|[ ] No `file:../` references in `package.json`
STEP|18|[ ] No native modules (`better-sqlite3`, `sharp`, `bcrypt`, etc.)
STEP|19|[ ] No unnecessary server frameworks (`express`, `ws`, `socket.io`)
STEP|20|[ ] Package from GitHub uses `#branch` suffix for latest commit
STEP|21|[ ] `npm ci` would work (ensure `package-lock.json` is committed)
STEP|22|**Don't install heavy deps "just in case."** If a feature doesn't need Express at runtime, don't add it. Next.js API routes handle all server logic.
STEP|23|**Don't use WebSocket on Vercel.** It doesn't work in serverless. Use REST polling (15-30s interval) or SWR with `refreshInterval`.
STEP|24|**Redeploy manually if auto-deploy stalls.** Vercel's GitHub integration sometimes skips pushes. Go to the dashboard and trigger manually.
STEP|25|**`next build` passing locally doesn't guarantee Vercel success.** The Vercel environment is Ubuntu-based with different native dependency support. Test with `npm ci && npm run build` to simulate CI.
PIT|**Don't install heavy deps "just in case."** If a feature doesn't need Express at runtime, don't add it. Next.js API routes handle all server logic.
PIT|**Don't use WebSocket on Vercel.** It doesn't work in serverless. Use REST polling (15-30s interval) or SWR with `refreshInterval`.
PIT|**Redeploy manually if auto-deploy stalls.** Vercel's GitHub integration sometimes skips pushes. Go to the dashboard and trigger manually.
PIT|**`next build` passing locally doesn't guarantee Vercel success.** The Vercel environment is Ubuntu-based with different native dependency support. Test with `npm ci && npm run build` to simulate CI.